  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Emperor Hirohito, 87, will be remembered for his first effective and the most courageous decision during his 62-year reign:
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Japan must surrender and end the Pacific conflict in WW II.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   He is generally portrayed as having played no significant role in Japan's war efforts.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   In the first 20 years of his reign, Hirohito was worshipped as a divinity.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   On January 1, 1945 he publicly renounced his divinity, enabling him to remain as the symbolic head of Japan and assuring
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   that he would not face charges as a war criminal.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   In post-WW II Japan, he was often viewed as a kind uncle.
  </a>
